title: Mitch McConnell
added: With the election victories of Democrats [[Raphael Warnock]] and [[Jon Ossoff]] in both a [[2020-21 United States Senate special election in Georgia|special]] and [[2020-21 United States Senate election in Georgia|regular]] election in [[Georgia (U.S. state)|Georgia]], respectively, McConnell is expected to return to the position of minority leader, as both Democrats' victories ensured a 50-50 tie in the Senate, which can be broken by [[Vice President of the United States|Vice President]]-elect [[Kamala Harris]].

title: Mitch McConnell
deleted: After the [[2020 United States Senate elections]], McConnell returned to the position of minority leader. In February 2021, in the [[second impeachment trial of Donald Trump]], McConnell voted to acquit due to an issue concerning Constitutional jurisdiction. However, McConnell said he believed Trump had engaged in a "disgraceful dereliction of duty" and "there is no question{{nbs}}... that President Trump is practically and morally responsible for provoking the event of that day."<ref>{{cite web|url= https://apnews.com/article/capitol-siege-donald-trump-impeachments-trump-impeachment-mitch-mcconnell-0a14d2e41e376331580b98a992f7d856|title= GOP's McConnell: Trump morally responsible for Jan. 6 attack|website= The Associated Press|access-date= February 13, 2021}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Roll Call Vote 117th Congress â€“ 1st Session |url=https://www.senate.gov/legislative/LIS/roll_call_lists/roll_call_vote_cfm.cfm?congress=117&session=1&vote=00059 |website=U.S. Senate |access-date=February 14, 2021}}</ref>
